class:: Disperser

summary:: Cascaded allpass filters

categories:: UGens>Filters

DESCRIPTION::

Cascaded Allpass Filters. 100% Twang.

CLASSMETHODS::

METHOD:: ar

ARGUMENT:: input
Audio input signal

ARGUMENT:: freq
Allpass filter cutoff frequency in Hz (20-20000)

ARGUMENT:: resonance
Filter resonance (0-1). Higher values create sharper phase transitions at the cutoff frequency

ARGUMENT:: mix
Dry/wet crossfade (0-1). 0 = completely dry, 1 = completely wet

ARGUMENT:: feedback
Feedback amount (0-1). Higher values create regenerative resonances and can make the disperser "ring"

returns:: Audio rate UGen.

EXAMPLES::

subsection::Basic Disperser

code::
(
{
	var sig = Impulse.ar(2);
	Disperser.ar(
		input: sig,
		freq: 500,
		resonance: 0.0,
		mix: 1.0,
		feedback: 0.0
	)!2;
}.play;
)
::

subsection::Phaser with Feedback
code::
(
{
	var sig = Saw.ar(110);
	Disperser.ar(
		input: sig,
		freq: SinOsc.kr(0.2).linlin(-1, 1, 200, 2000),
		resonance: MouseY.kr(0, 0.5),
		mix: 1.0,
		feedback: MouseX.kr(0, 0.95)
	)!2 * 0.1;
}.play;
)
::